{"id":"2033","name":"yazoo-outgrows-marathon-building-heading-to-gulch","title":"Yazoo Outgrows Marathon Building, Heading To Gulch","author":"Morgan Levy","date":"2009-07-08T10:52:00-05:00","tags":["beer","brewery","germantown","gulch","marathon building","taproom","yazoo"],"categories":["Food &amp; Drink","News"],"contentEncoded":"<div class=\"post-image-wrapper -wrapper\">       \t\t\t\t\t                    <img class=\"post-image portrait\" src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/plugins/fresh-page/thirdparty/phpthumb/phpThumb.php?src=http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/files_flutter/1247068251_1_1_1_2_post-image.jpg&amp;w=322&amp;&amp;aoe=1\">              \t\t\t\t\t    <div class=\"post-image-footer\">&#xA0;</div>\t\t\t\t\t  </div>\t\t\t\t\t  \t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"greet_block\"><noscript><div class=\"greet_block wpgb_cornered\"><div class=\"greet_text\"><div class=\"greet_image\"><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/feed/rss/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-greet-box/images/rss_icon.png\" alt=\"WP Greet Box icon\"></a></div>Hello there! If you&apos;re new to Nashvillest, you might want to <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/nashvillest\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>subscribe to our RSS feed</strong></a> to make sure you don&apos;t miss anything! We&apos;re also on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/nashvillest\" target=\"blank\"><strong>Twitter</strong></a> if you&apos;d like to join us there!<div style=\"clear:both\"></div><div class=\"greet_block_powered_by\">Powered by <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/projects/wordpress-plugins/wp-greet-box-wordpress-plugin/\" title=\"WP Greet Box WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WP Greet Box</a> <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/\" title=\"WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WordPress Plugin</a></div><div style=\"clear:both\"></div></div></div></noscript></div><p>Though we love <a href=\"http://www.yazoobrew.com\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.yazoobrew.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Yazoo Brewing&#x2019;s</a> space in the Marathon Building, after taking a tour of the brewery late last year, we realized how cramped they are back there. And if <a href=\"http://yazoobrew.blogspot.com/2009/07/yazoo-in-gulch.html\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;yazoobrew.blogspot.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">today&#x2019;s announcement</a> that Yazoo is packing up and moving to a larger space in the Gulch means more Yazoo for us, well, you won&#x2019;t find any complaints here!</p><p>Yazoo Brewing has already started construction at 910 Division, a space that is four times bigger than their current location. Owner (and brewmaster extraordinaire) Linus Hall plans to have the new brewery and taproom open by the beginning of 2010.</p><p>How do you feel about the move? We hold the Marathon Building near and dear to our hearts, but sometimes you gotta do what you gotta do.</p><p>Related posts:<ol><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2010/02/19/make-hoppy-history-yazoo-auctioning-off-first-pint-in-new-brewery/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Make Hoppy History: Yazoo Auctioning Off First Pint In New Brewery\">Make Hoppy History: Yazoo Auctioning Off First Pint In New Brewery</a></li><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2009/11/18/pour-up-yazoo-tweet-up-tonight-at-the-melrose-pub/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Pour Up: Yazoo Tweet-Up Tonight At The Melrose Pub\">Pour Up: Yazoo Tweet-Up Tonight At The Melrose Pub</a></li><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2008/07/02/whats-going-on-with-the-gulch/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: What&#x2019;s Going On With The Gulch?\">What&#x2019;s Going On With The Gulch?</a></li><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2009/11/04/clear-the-roads-cool-springs-chuys-open-for-business-and-heading-for-the-boro/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: C